        <p>Travel is one of the few areas where a little planning genuinely halves the cost. The families paying double aren't getting a better trip — they just booked at the wrong time with the wrong tools. Here's how to be on the cheaper side of that.</p>

        <h2>Let flight deals come to you</h2>
        <p>The single biggest cost of most trips is airfare, and prices swing wildly. Instead of checking manually, use a deal-alert service that watches routes from your home airport and emails you when a fare drops.</p>

